# SDG Hub Backend - Environment Variables
# ============================================================================
# SECURITY BEST PRACTICES:
# 1. Copy this file to backend/.env (which is git-ignored)
# 2. Add your actual API keys to backend/.env
# 3. Reference them in the UI using "env:VARIABLE_NAME" format
# 4. NEVER commit .env or share it with others
# ============================================================================

# OpenAI API Key
# Usage in UI: Enter "env:OPENAI_API_KEY" in the API Key field
OPENAI_API_KEY=your-openai-key-here

# Anthropic (Claude) API Key
# Usage in UI: Enter "env:ANTHROPIC_API_KEY" in the API Key field
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your-anthropic-key-here

# Local vLLM Server (if using authentication)
# Usage in UI: Enter "env:VLLM_API_KEY" or just use "EMPTY"
VLLM_API_KEY=EMPTY

# Other LLM Provider Keys
# Add any other API keys you need below

# Cohere API Key
# COHERE_API_KEY=your-cohere-key-here

# Hugging Face API Key
# HUGGINGFACE_API_KEY=your-hf-key-here

# Together AI API Key
# TOGETHERAI_API_KEY=your-together-key-here

# ============================================================================
# HOW TO USE:
# ============================================================================
# 
# 1. Setup (one time):
#    cd backend
#    cp ../.env.example .env
#    # Edit .env with your actual keys
#
# 2. In the UI:
#    - API Key field: Enter "env:OPENAI_API_KEY" (not the actual key)
#    - The backend will automatically resolve the environment variable
#
# 3. Benefits:
#    ✓ API keys never stored in configurations
#    ✓ API keys never sent over the network  
#    ✓ Can share configurations safely
#    ✓ Easy to rotate keys (just update .env)
# ============================================================================
